{
  "texts": [
    "The risks or defects that may arise in AI systems depend on the system's function and intended area of use.",
    "While AI may be considered high-risk in certain domains, the technology may potentially reduce overall risks in some areas.",
    "62 Courts in product liability lawsuits will be tasked with determining the acceptable level of safety for AI systems (Lemley and Casey, 2019).",
    "They must decide how frequently and under which circumstances AI is allowed to fail before it is deemed defective (Whittam, 2022, 5).",
    "This paper argues that such defects will more often stem from design defects than from manufacturing defects, as compared to traditional products."
  ]
}